net.jxta.content
Interface ContentService

All Superinterfaces:
ContentProvider, ContentProviderSPI, Module, Service
All Known Implementing Classes:
ContentServiceImpl
public interface ContentService
extends ContentProviderSPI

The ContentService is intended to be the end-user's main access point when working with Content and Content transfers. It provides the ability to leverage multiple ContentProvider implementations concurrently, providing resilience and failover in the event that one or more ContentProvider implementations fail to perform the requested task(s) properly.

The ability to enumerate the list of providers is in place to allow for programatic removal of providers which may not have been programatically added (e.g., added via the Jar SPI mechanism), default implementation(s) included.

ContentService implementations supporting multiple provider implementations may choose to defer the startup of the providers until the time of first use.

See Also:
ContentProvider

removeContentProvider

void removeContentProvider(ContentProvider provider)
Removes a provider instance. If transfers are already underway by the time this method is called, they will continue to use the provider until the transfer has completed or has been terminated.

Parameters:
provider - instance to remove.

getContentProviders

List<ContentProvider> getContentProviders()
Returns a list of content service provider instances underlying this service. This method returns all registered provider instances, including those which have not been initialized and/or started. If you wish to obtain a list of only those providers which have successfully started and are available for use, use the getActiveContentProviders() method form instead.

Returns:
list of content providers registered with this service. If no providers are registered, this method return an empty list.

getActiveContentProviders

List<ContentProvider> getActiveContentProviders()
Returns a list of content service provider instances underlying this service which have been started and are available for use. Since this method only returns the provider instance which have successfully made it through intialization, it will not be a complete list of all registered providers. Also, a ContentService implementation may choose to defer the initialization of it's underlying provider instances (if any) until the time of use. In this case, this method would return an empty list until after the first use.

ContentService instances which defer the starting of the providers until first use should treat a call to this method as a first use.

Returns:
list of content providers registered with this service. If no providers are active, this method returns an empty list.
